HEADWORD: Invigorate
<hw>In*vig"or*ate</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧n*v⟦icr⟧g"⟦etil⟧r*⟦amac⟧t)</pr>,
<pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Invigorated</conjf>
<pr>(⟦icr⟧n*v⟦icr⟧g"⟦etil⟧r*⟦amac⟧`t⟦ecr⟧d)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Invigorating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>vigor</ets>.]</ety> <def>To give vigor to; to
strengthen; to animate; to give life and energy to.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Christian graces and virtues they can not be, unless fed,
<qex>invigorated</qex>, and animated by universal charity.</q>
<rj><qau>Atterbury.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To refresh; animate; exhilarate;
stimulate.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Invigoration</ent>⟦br⟧
